        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 23 at 1:21PM CDT by NWS Topeka KS</headline>
        <description>At 121 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles northeast of Green, moving northeast at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Hail damage to outdoor objects and vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Green.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
